other_tests.findings: Atelectasis at both lung bases, small right and trace left pleural effusions, heterogeneous enhancement of the liver, hyperenhancement around the gallbladder and in the left hepatic lobe, mild central periportal edema, attenuated branches of the right anterior portal vein suggesting phlebitis, distended gallbladder with multiple gallstones and wall thickening, no evidence of perforation, small hiatal hernia.
